my neighbors' dogs are in horrible condidtion what should i do we moved to a new state from california last year only to discover the horrible conditions for local animals the only non kill shelter for seven surrounding counties is full to capacity not accepting any more animals the local animal shelter puts down nearly three quarters of all the animals it receives killing animals last month their staff is unfriendly and unwelcoming of volunteers abandoned looking barns near the road by my home are known for dog abandonment i've rescued four dogs from there myself unfortunately the land's owner will shoot any strays he sees another symptom of the poor care law enforcement officers can only remove an animal if it is proven they receive inadequate food water and or shelter there in lies my problem my neighbors have two large dogs both dogs are walking mats i've never seen anything like it they have difficulty moving they barely made it through the heat of the recent drought is there anything i can do talk to your neiborghs about it ask if you can shave them or take them to the groomer update and i will add more Domestic rabbit Feral Golden Retriever Feral cat Dog People for the Ethical Treatment of Animals Rescue group Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Animal rights Cat Rais massacre Livestock Hunting Dairy Criticism of government response to Hurricane Katrina Animal testing Socialization 2005 Kashmir earthquake Renewable energy Pet skunk Professional wrestling aerial techniques Brown Bear Emergency preparedness Obedience training Organic farming Animal euthanasia Constitution of the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus First aid Great Hanshin earthquake Community emergency response team Anorexia nervosa Effect of Hurricane Katrina on New Orleans Hamster Disaster RuneScape quests Burma Campaign A Canticle for Leibowitz Kodocha USS Williamson (DD-244) Dog training Breastfeeding Sheep husbandry Search and rescue Richard Chase Survival skills Firefighter Hiking Platoon (film) D